<br />
     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Trying to make up a deck that would not give up too much twilight ever, and avoid any Skirmishes<br />
through the first move.<br />
Bid low, but better to go first.<br />
After Buckleberry, try to get Aragorn established<br />
with as much of his goodies as possible, hopefully a No Stranger and an Athelas<br />
Sam should show up to help with any burdens.<br />
Get a sword on Merry and hopefully Sting and the Mithril Coat on Frodo. Extra Sam just in case. Plenty of healing with Aragorn and Athelas.<br />
Bounder just in case he&#39;s needed and Tharin to help with taking archery or skirmish wounds.<br />
Able Guide helps to double move to jump ahead.<br />
And maybe Boromir will show up to help with the Balrog.<br />
The Minion mix seems to work well together.<br />
Get to reuse the Goblin Marksmen with Host of Thousands.<br />
Nazguls and Lurtz with some low cost Uruks and weather spells help to create some hurt, and the Cave Troll always seems to pop up when you need him.<br />
I wanted to keep this deck as small as possible,<br />
and it works well for me.<br />
 Could start with Boromir and Merry instead with couple of site changes.<br />
